data.enText: used to introduce some new information that adds to or supports what you have said previously

data.chText: 他是一位有才华的艺术家，同时也是颇有名气的作家。
data.enText: A talented artist, he was, moreover, a writer of some note.

example: computer chess games are getting cheaper all the tim
what is more, there's no sign of a change

value.def: You use moreover to introduce a piece of information that adds to or supports the previous statement.

example.ex: She saw that there was indeed a man immediately behind her. Moreover, he was observing her strangely...
example.tran: 她看见真有一个男的紧跟在她身后，而且在怪异地注视自己。

example.ex: The young find everything so simple. The young, moreover, see it as their duty to be happy and do their best to be so.
example.tran: 年轻人觉得每件事都那么简单;而且，他们把幸福视为自己的责任，并努力去实现幸福。
